2026-06-30T15:42:25 | INFO | INTERACTION {"session_id": "a92d28fbd1414045a7dd3b9dbe3d9aa1", "question": "What are the minimum entry requirements for undergraduate degree programmes at UDSM?", "answer": "According to the University of Dar es Salaam's policy, as stated in Box 35091 DAR ES SALAAM EMAIL: udasa@udsm.ac.tz and Undergraduate Prospectus - 2022/2023 on page 30, the minimum entry requirements for undergraduate degree programmes are as follows:\n- The course must be at a level equivalent to UDSM's Bachelor's Degree courses. Intermediate Diploma or Higher Diploma levels of study do not meet this requirement and hence cannot substitute. \n- There needs to have a theoretical component involving final examinations, meaning that clinical-based or practical only programs are ineligible for these degree programmes as per UDSM policy (Box 35091). Furthermore, the course content must be at least 75% similar to that of the UDSM programme.\n- The minimum number of students required is ten; however, departments wishing to run a programme with fewer than ten can obtain special permission from the Deputy Vice Chancellor (Academic). However, it's also stated in Undergraduate Prospectus - 2022/2023 that applicants from countries following an 8-4-4 education system need to complete at least one year of study at a university recognized by the UDSM Senate. This would not be directly applicable here as we're discussing undergraduate programme entry requirements, but it can give some context regarding international student policies which may influence overall admission processes within UDSM (Undergraduate Prospectus - 2022/2023 on page 17-18).\n   \nPlease note that these are the general guidelines. Some specific programs might have additional requirements, so I recommend reaching out to your department for more detailed information or directly contacting UDSM's admissions office if you need further clarification regarding any particular programmes (Undergraduate Prospectus - 2022/2023).", "source": "LLM", "response_time": 19.05, "retrieved_context": ["e of the same level as that of UDSM i.e. Bachelors degree course for undergraduate degree courses. Courses at intermediate levels such as Advanced Diploma, or Higher Diploma levels are not acceptable. 4.2 The course must have a theoretical component i.e. involving final examination, excluding clinical-based or practical only courses. 4.3 Course content must be at least 75% similar to that of the UDSM course. 4.4 The number of teaching hours used to cover the course must not be less than 75% of t", "BOX 35091 DAR ES SALAAM EMAIL: udasa@udsm.ac.tz\nNIL NIL\n\nUndergraduate Prospectus - 2022/2023 30\nUNDERGRADUATE PROGRAMMES WHICH ARE OFFERED FOR THE UNIVERSITY CERTIFICATES, DIPLOMAS AND DEGREES AWARDS The minimum number of students required for any particular undergraduate programme to run shall be ten. Departments wishing to run programmes with less than ten students shall first obtain special permission from the Deputy Vice-Chancellor (Academic). The set minimum number of students is subject", "less than Second class/Credit level or B grade obtained from a college which is fully registered by NACTE and approved by a the UDSM Senate. For Diploma that are further classified into Upper and Lower classes, the requirement shall be an Upper Second class or B+ average. Note: Applicants from countries which follow an 8-4-4 education system need to complete at least one year of study at a university in their own countries before they can be considered for admission into the University of Dar es"]}
