2026-06-30T17:11:28 | INFO | INTERACTION {"session_id": "963356f7cd2d4da7bdbc8a359b73010e", "question": "how to register in course", "answer": "To register for a course at the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM), please follow these steps:  \n1. Visit your school's UDSM registration website or contact the administration office directly if you havenâ€™t done so yet this year as all new full-time students should do it before the beginning of their first semester, which is typically at the start of a standard academic term in Tanzania (September to December).  \n2. Select your preferred course(s) from the available options provided by UDSM's curriculum for each discipline you are interested in pursuing further education or specialization within that year and semester, ensuring these courses meet any core requirements as stated on page 13 of the Student Handbook (2.2).  \n3. Complete your online registration process if required by clicking through prompts which direct you to input necessary personal details such as student ID number, contact information, etc., or register in person for more complex situations based on UDSMâ€™s procedures outlined under \"Registration Procedures\" (Section 12).\n4. After completing the selection of courses and payment confirmation if mandated by the university's policy that states 'payment to the University is deemed as adequate registration for requisite examinations in a particular course' (Context from UDSM documents), your enrollment will be confirmed, ensuring you are registered appropriately within the academic calendar.  \n5. For continuing students or those who had an unfortunate circumstance prevent them to register at the end of their previous yearâ€™s semester as mentioned in section 2 (Registration for Courses), they must apply to higher administration and provide special reasons, which will then be considered on a case-by-case basis.  \n6. Always keep your personal details up-to-date within UDSM systems by notifying the relevant office of any changes as promptly as possible following university guidelines for maintaining accurate academic records (General Student Policies).", "source": "LLM", "response_time": 26.84, "retrieved_context": ["o special registration of candidates for examinations. Registration and payment to the University of all required or prescribed fees by a candidate for a course of study shall be deemed as adequate registration for the requisite examinations in the particular course of study. 2. Registration for Courses 2.1 All new full-time students shall register for courses at the beginning of the first semester of an academic year and continuing students shall register for courses at the end of an academic y", "shall be the Friday of the second week after the beginning of the semester. Course registration at the beginning of the semester for continuing students shall only be allowed under special circumstances which prevented them from registering at the end of the year. 2.2 A student who has registered for a course but who wishes to withdraw from that course must apply to the Head/Dean/Director/Principal, as the case may be, of the unit hosting the programme through the Head of the course offering De", "addition to core courses required for a particular academic year, a student in the 2nd, 3rd and 4th Year of study, shall be required to meet the minimum prescribed credits from the optional courses on offer. 13.4 Before the end of each academic year 1st, 2nd and 3rd Year students shall select and register his or her course programme for the following academic year. Course registration shall be done online using the electronic course registration system or as determined by the Dean. 13.5 Two wee"]}
