2026-06-30T18:32:59 | INFO | INTERACTION {"session_id": "3c715859495140b18a20243962c98cf0", "question": "How do I register for courses?", "answer": "To register for a course at the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM), you should follow these steps: [1] Visit the UDSM Registrar's Office website to access the registration system. This can typically be found in your university portal or directly from their official domain, which is usually something like uism.edu.tn/registrationsystem/.\n[2] Log into your student account using your unique username and password provided by UDSM upon enrollment [3] Select 'Register for Courses' option within the system; this can vary slightly depending on how individual universities categorize these options, but it generally involves navigating through a dropdown menu or link to find courses you wish to take.\n[4] Search and select your desired course by its code number from either UDSMâ€™s academic catalog [5] Add the selected course(s) along with any prerequisite requirements as indicated on the respective departments' websites if necessaryâ€”UDSM has detailed departmental information that can be found through their dedicated sections online.\n[6] Confirm your selections and submit them for processing; you may receive a confirmation email or notification directly in UDSMâ€™s student portal informing you of successful registration [7] If there are any issues during the process, contact the Registrar's Office by phone or visit their office to resolve conflicts promptly.\nFor specific policies and details about course registrations, please refer to UDSM policy documents such as 'Regulations on Academic Affairs', particularly section 3-10 concerning academic registration procedures: [UDSM Policy Document Link].", "source": "LLM", "response_time": 15.67, "retrieved_context": []}
