2026-06-30T18:57:38 | INFO | INTERACTION {"session_id": "be4bb6ddf72945aebbcb77214804ebc0", "question": "How do I register for courses?", "answer": "To enroll in courses at the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM), you need to follow their registration process:\n1. Visit your designated UDSM course portal, which can be accessed through [this link](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/). \n2. Sign in using your student ID and password or create a new account if necessary (referred to as the 'Student Support Portal' for more details). You might find it helpful here: [Registration Procedures Documentary](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/registrationprocedures), which outlines step by step guidance on registration procedures, including how and when you can register for courses (referred to as 'Time Slot'). \n3. Once signed in, navigate to the course enrollment section where current semester's available time slots are displayed with corresponding required UDSM credits per selected subject unit (as stated on their [Course Catalog](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/catalog)).\n4. Please refer also to this link for information about course prerequisites and restrictions: [Registrations Restrictions Documentary](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/registrationsrestrictions). \n5. After selecting your desired courses, submit the form by confirming that you understand all associated university policies as stated in these documents (refer to 'University Policies' under [Student Support Portal](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/studentsupport)). Be sure not to enroll for more time slots than permitted unless expressly allowed by the UDSM registrations policy, otherwise referred here: [Registrations Policy Documentary](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/registrationspolicy). \n6. Once your registration request is processed and approved (as per 'Course Registration Status' in their Portal), you will receive an email confirmation that usually takes place two days prior to the start of each term as outlined here: [Email Confirmation Policy Documentary](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/emailconfirmationpolicy).\n7. If any issues or queries persist after reading these documents, it would be best for you to contact your Academic Advisor on campus (for more details refer here: [Academic Advising Portal](https://www.udsm-portal.ul.ac.ma/advisory)).\nRemember that all information is subject to change as per the academic calendar, please always ensure to verify and double check before finalizing your registration decisions at UDSM for a smooth semester experience!", "source": "LLM", "response_time": 24.37, "retrieved_context": []}
