2026-06-30T19:03:14 | INFO | INTERACTION {"session_id": "edc6c4e7f6b64a70a59d69070ac3105b", "question": "How do I pay tuition fees?", "answer": "To make a payment for your tuition fees at the University of Dar es Salaam, you can visit our official UDSM bank account or use an approved online portal if available. Please refer to the latest university guidelines on fee payment methods and deadlines which are published annually in the student handbook (UG Student Handbook). If these options aren't clear to you or require additional help, I recommend reaching out directly to our Financial Services office for personalized assistance.\n\nUnfortunately, as per my design guidelines, there is no specific context provided within this system that details tuition fee payment procedures at the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM). However, UDM students are typically required to pay their fees through a combination of bank transfers and online platforms. It's always advisable for any student with financial inquiries related to university services like this one, especially when seeking accurate information about the payment process at an institution such as our esteemed University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM), is to contact directly UDMâ€™s Financial Services office or check their official guidelines and policies. \n\nRemember that financial procedures can change yearly, so it's important always to stay updated with the latest information from university sources like student handbooks or dedicated finance department offices for accurate guidance on matters related to tuition payments at UDSM University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM).", "source": "LLM", "response_time": 19.35, "retrieved_context": []}
