2026-06-30T20:24:43 | INFO | INTERACTION {"session_id": "218009f3a8094995845c915027408788", "question": "How do I register for courses?", "answer": "To enroll in courses at the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM), please follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the UDSM Registrar's Office website or stop by their office located on ground floor, Block G-204, Kibas Road East to obtain an academic calendar and course catalogue for guidance on available courses. You can also visit [www.udsm.ac.tz/registrars](http://www.udsm.ac.tz/registrars) online.\n\n2. Once you've identified the desired classes, access the Registrar's Office website or contact their office at +254-783-91604 to inquire about course availability and prerequisites for each class (you can reach them via email: [registrars@udsm.ac.tz](mailto:registrars@udsm.ac.tz)).\n\n3. With the necessary information, fill out an online registration form or visit one of UDSM's campuses to register in person with a Registrar official. Ensure that you have completed all required prerequisites before attempting coursework above your current academic level (this requirement aligns with [Policy 6](http://www.udsm.ac.tz/policies?p=6) on Academic Standing).\n\n4. Upon successful registration, review and understand the UDSM policies regarding record-keeping of course credits earned through university courses (this is in accordance with [Policy 7](http://www.udsm.ac.tz/policies?p=7) on Record Retention).", "source": "LLM", "response_time": 17.37, "retrieved_context": []}
