2026-06-30T20:40:58 | INFO | INTERACTION {"session_id": "357d534a262b458cb72ee4032427dff7", "question": "How do I register for courses?", "answer": "To enroll in courses at the University of Dar es Salaam (UDSM), you need to follow their registration process which is outlined on UDSM's official website under Academic Policies and Procedures. Generally, students are required to sign up for classes during designated periods through an online portal provided by UDSM but please confirm the exact steps as this might vary from year to year or due to any changes in their policies. \n\nHowever, I don't have specific details about course registration at your current request time based on my knowledge cutoff date and without access to real-time data updates of university practices which may change over time. Please check the latest guidelines available from UDSM directly or get assistance through student services for accurate information tailored specifically for you as a prospective, enrolling, or currently registered student at UDSM. \n\nFor further help and to ensure your course registration is successful:\n1. Visit www.udsm.go.tz/ (or the appropriate university domain) where official guidelines are provided by UDSM administration for current students as well as prospective ones about enrollment procedures, including how and when to register courses. \n2. Review their academic calendar regularly so you're aware of key dates like start date, end date, exam schedules which align with registration deadlines. \n3. Contact the Student Affairs Office at UDSM for personalized guidance if needed as they provide one-on-one assistance to students about enrollment and course selection process among other university services. You can reach them through their official communication channels including email, phone calls or scheduled appointments based on availability of faculty/staff members assisting with these queries.", "source": "LLM", "response_time": 18.42, "retrieved_context": []}
